                <h2>The following data collection forms are available:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Water Temperature Data Logger Form</li>
                    <li>Fish Stocking Form</li>
                    <li>Electrofishing Forms</li>
                    <li>Individual Fish Measurements Form</li>
                    <li>Aquatic Habitat Enhancement / Restoration Form</li>
                    <li>Environmental Stream Assessment</li>
                    <li>Stream Habitat Survey</li>
                    <li>Water Flow Calculation Form</li>
                </ul>   
                <p>These forms provide space to record many important details related to the specific activity, including particulars on the sampling site and methods used. Users should complete all applicable spaces on the forms. Accurately identifying the location of the activity is particularly important. Please record GPS coordinates if available, water body identification numbers (from NB Aquatic Data Warehouse), and textual descriptions. Also, note the locations on a 1:50,000 topographic map. The download package includes a manual for completing the forms.</p>
